Six people sustained serious to minor injuries after a taxi collided with a vehicle on Rivonia road and corner North road in Sandton on Sunday.According to paramedics the accident happened this morning at about 07:00am.All injured were stabilised on scene and thereafter transported to a nearby hospital for further medical care.The exact detail as to how the accident happened will form part of a SAPS investigation and comment. Netcare911 paramedics worked alongside other services on scene.-TNA Reporter